pull_request.title: Bump oqs-sys/liboqs from `7efdb91` to `f167391`
pull_request.body:
Bumps [oqs-sys/liboqs](https://github.com/Open-Quantum-Safe/liboqs) from `7efdb91` to `f167391`.
Commits
  • f167391 KeccakP-1600times4/avx2: Switch a memmove to a memcpy for musl libc (#972)
  • 7b56fa8 Remove AES decryption functions (#970)
  • 008ba89 Don't do feature detection inside a tight loop (#969)
  • aa076bb oqsconfig.h.cmake: add missing OQS_ENABLE_SHA3_xkcp_low_avx2 line (#968)
  • 44fe8fd SIKE/CMake: recognize both x64+BMI2 and x64+BMI2+ADX (#965)
  • efd7b19 Speed up ARM jobs in CI (#964)
  • See full diff in compare view

Dependabot will resolve any conflicts with this PR as long as you don't alter it yourself. You can also trigger a rebase manually by commenting `@dependabot rebase`. [//]: # (dependabot-automerge-start) [//]: # (dependabot-automerge-end) ---

You can achieve the same result by closing it manually - `@dependabot ignore this major version` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this major version (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot ignore this minor version` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this minor version (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself) - `@dependabot ignore this dependency` will close this PR and stop Dependabot creating any more for this dependency (unless you reopen the PR or upgrade to it yourself)

pull_request.title: Enable OQS OPENSSL for UEFI/EDKII.
pull_request.body:
1) Add OPENSSL_NO_CMS around CMS_SignerInfo_get0_algs().
Otherwise, it causes UEFI EDKII link failure.

2) Add #include <openssl/rsa.h> for RSA_PKCS1_PADDING.
Otherwise, it causes UEFI EDKII build failure.

Signed-off-by: Jiewen Yao <jiewen.yao@intel.com>

pull_request.title: Improved signing support
pull_request.body:
Fixes #295 adding support for any digest algorithm; SHA512 remains default if nothing else is specified.
Also removes manual CI approval from upstream-initiated builds.

- [x] documentation is added or updated
- [x] tests are added or updated
